2. Consumer Commodities 


The FPLA defines consumer commodities as being any food, drug, device, or cosmetic and any other article, product
or commodity of any kind or class which is customarily produced or distributed for sale through retail sales agencies
or instrumentalities for consumption by individuals, or use by individuals for purposes of personal care or in the
performance of services ordinarily rendered within the household, and which usually is consumed or expended in the
course of such consumption or use.

